.TH NHOUSER 8 "@RELEASEDATE@" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "Nhopkg Manual"
.SH NAME
nhouser \- idempotent system user and group creation for nhopkg
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nhouser
\fB\-\-check\fR|\fB\-\-create\fR \fB\-\-user\fR \fIname\fR [options]
.br
.B nhouser
\fB\-\-check\fR|\fB\-\-create\fR \fB\-\-group\fR \fIname\fR [\fB\-\-gid\fR \fIgid\fR]
.br
.B nhouser
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
.br
.B nhouser
\fB\-\-version\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBnhouser\fR creates or checks system users and groups idempotently. It is
designed to be called from \fBnpostinstall()\fR in nhoid recipes to ensure
required system users and groups exist before a package's service is started.
.P
One of \fB\-\-check\fR or \fB\-\-create\fR is required.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B \-\-check
Check if the specified user or group exists. Returns success (exit 0) if
found, failure (exit 1) if not found.
.TP
.B \-\-create
Create the specified user or group. If the user/group already exists, does
nothing (idempotent).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-user \fIname\fR
User name to check or create.
.TP
.B \-\-uid \fIuid\fR
Numeric user ID.
.TP
.B \-\-uname \fIcomment\fR
GECOS comment field for the user.
.TP
.B \-\-udir \fIpath\fR
Home directory for the user.
.TP
.B \-\-shell \fIpath\fR
Login shell for the user.
.TP
.B \-\-group \fIname\fR
Group name to check or create.
.TP
.B \-\-gid \fIgid\fR
Numeric group ID.
.TP
.B \-\-groups \fI"g1,g2"\fR
Comma-separated list of supplementary groups.
.TP
.B \-\-locked
Lock the user account immediately after creation (calls \fBpasswd \-l\fR).
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Verbose output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create a system user for cups
.B nhouser \-\-create \-\-user cups \-\-uid 216 \-\-udir /dev/null \-\-shell /bin/false
.TP
Check if a user exists
.B nhouser \-\-check \-\-user cups
.TP
Create a system group
.B nhouser \-\-create \-\-group lp \-\-gid 19
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nhopkg (8),
.BR nhopkg.conf (5),
.BR nhopkg-src (8)
